| Client & server
| {{Yes}}
| {{Yes}}
| {{Yes}}
| {{Yes}}{{Efn | Remote Desktop Services are single user only. Local screen is locked when remote user connects and local user can not view remote user's activities. Remote user is disconnected when local user logs in. Terminal Services use multiple independent desktops. Local user views its own desktop and can not view remote users' activities. Local user is not notified when remote user connects.}}
| {{Yes}}{{Efn | Provided the server is running Windows 2008 or later.}}
| {{Yes}}{{Efn | Assistance mode uses a separate client named MSRA (Microsoft Remote Assistance). Remote user must approve your access in assistance mode.}}
| {{Yes}}{{Efn | Access approval is always requested in assistance mode and never in remote access mode.}}
